Class DSMediaType

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.humatic.dsj.DSMediaType
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    DSFilterInfo.DSMediaFormat

    public class DSMediaType
extends java.lang.Object
    DSMediaType loosely wraps DirectShow's AM_MEDIA_TYPE structure. See msdn documentation

    • Constructor Detail

      • DSMediaType

        public DSMediaType()

      • DSMediaType

        public DSMediaType(int majorType,
           int subType,
           int formatType)
        Creates a basic media type object. %majorType refers to the kind of media described (i.e. Video, Audio, stream) and should use one of the MT_ constants. %subtype describes the actual format (for example MP4V or WMV9 for video, PCM or mp3 for audio) and uses the VST_, AST_ or SST_ subtypes or an int representation of a FourCharCode. %formattype describes the layout of the native Mediatype structure's data, for details refer to DirectShow's AM_MEDIA_TYPE documentation.

      • setFormatBlock

        public void setFormatBlock(byte[] fb)
        DSMediaType's format block is a variable size byte array, which for video and stream types consists of a 16 byte block used internally plus a variable size block used for codec specific data, such as sequence headers, SPS/PPS etc. For audiotypes size and usage depend on the format, there is no reserved space.

      • getExtendedField

        public int getExtendedField(int fieldID)
        Returns the value of a field that not all native media types have and which may therefore not be set. This relates to VideoInfo2, MPEG2VideoInfo and WaveFormatExtensible formats. Field IDs are defined as VX_ and AX_ constants. Some common, but less often used fields are also included here.
